"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381849","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-06-26","<p>Data is publically available at the link below:</p><p> </p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/local-authority-revenue-expenditure-and-financing</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2015-06-26T13:19:48.49Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381849/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381849/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381849/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-17","Council Tax Reduction Schemes: Barking and Dagenham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many people in the London Borough of Barking and Dagenham were in receipt of council tax support in (a) 2014-15 and (b) 2013-14.","false","Biography information for Dame Margaret Hodge","Barking","Margaret Hodge","3016"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381850","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-06-24","<p>This information is not held centrally. <br><br>The Department for Communities and Local Government collects quarterly data on temporary accommodation from all local authorities in England on the P1E form. Whilst this form collects data on the numbers of households that local authorities have provided with temporary accommodation in another district, it does not request details of which authorities they have been placed in.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2015-06-24T11:41:40.407Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381850/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381850/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381850/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-17","Temporary Accommodation: Barking and Dagenham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many households in temporary accommodation are housed by other London authorities in the London Borough of Barking and Dagenham.","false","Biography information for Dame Margaret Hodge","Barking","Margaret Hodge","2992"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381851","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-06-26","<p>The latest figure, for 1 April 2014, is published by the Department as part of the local authority housing statistics and is available at:<br><br>https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/local-authority-housing-statistics-data-returns-for-2013-to-2014</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2015-06-26T13:16:22.22Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381851/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381851/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381851/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-17","Social Rented Housing: Barking and Dagenham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many households on the social housing waiting list in the London Borough of Barking and Dagenham require a one bedroom property.","false","Biography information for Dame Margaret Hodge","Barking","Margaret Hodge","2993"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381852","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-23","<p /> <p><strong> </strong></p><p>The information requested is not available for March 2013.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>Council Tax Benefit (CTB) was abolished in April 2013 and replaced by a system of localised support. In England, the Department for Communities and Local Government is now responsible for statistics. The Scottish and Welsh Governments have similar responsibility.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>The available information relating to Council Tax Benefit up to February 2013 is shown in Table 10 of the publication available at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/housing-benefit-and-council-tax-benefit-caseload-statistics-published-from-november-2008-to-present" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/housing-benefit-and-council-tax-benefit-caseload-statistics-published-from-november-2008-to-present</a></p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-06-23T15:32:01.913Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381852/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381852/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381852/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-17","Council Tax Benefits: Barking and Dagenham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people were in receipt of council tax benefit in March 2013 in the London Borough of Barking and Dagenham.","false","Biography information for Dame Margaret Hodge","Barking","Margaret Hodge","3014"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381853","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-23","<p>The information requested in all four questions above is published and available at:</p><p><a href="https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/" target="_blank">https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk</a></p><p>Guidance on how to extract the information required can be found at:</p><p><a href="https://sw.stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/webapi/online-help/Getting-Started---SuperWEB2.html" target="_blank">https://sw.stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/webapi/online-help/Getting-Started---SuperWEB2.html</a></p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","2969 ; 3015 ; 3025","2015-06-23T15:35:01.567Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381853/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381853/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381853/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-17","Housing Benefit: Barking and Dagenham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people were in receipt of housing benefit in (a) 2014-15, (b) 2013-14, (c) 2012-13, (d) 2011-12 and (e) 2010-11 in the London Borough of Barking and Dagenham.","false","Biography information for Dame Margaret Hodge","Barking","Margaret Hodge","3021"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381854","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-22","<p /> <p>The available information on average (median) waiting times, at a national level, has been published and is available from the Personal Independence Payment statistics home page: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/personal-independence-payment-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/personal-independence-payment-statistics</a>. The Department is assessing the quality of the clearance time data at lower geographical levels and is considering the future release of such information into the public domain. These statistics will be published when they are ready, with the release pre-announced in line with United Kingdom Statistics Authority release protocols.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-06-22T14:52:33.247Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381854/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381854/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381854/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-17","Personal Independence Payment: Barking and Dagenham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the average length of time was that an applicant waited for a personal independence payment assessment in the London Borough of Barking and Dagenham in the most recent period for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Dame Margaret Hodge","Barking","Margaret Hodge","3020"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381855","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-23","<p /> <p>The information as requested is not available.</p><p> </p><p>The Information for those in work is only available for Housing Benefit (HB) recipients whose claim is not passported: that is for those who do not receive either income support, Jobseeker’s Allowance (Income-Based), Employment and Support Allowance (Income-Based), or Pension Credit (Guaranteed Credit). This information can be found at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/" target="_blank">https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk</a></p><p>Guidance on how to extract the information required can be found at:</p><p><a href="https://sw.stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/webapi/online-help/Getting-Started---SuperWEB2.html" target="_blank">https://sw.stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/webapi/online-help/Getting-Started---SuperWEB2.html</a></p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-06-23T14:57:34.823Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381855/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381855/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381855/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-17","Housing Benefit: Barking and Dagenham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many housing benefit claimants there were in employment in the London Borough of Barking and Dagenham in (a) 2014-15, (b) 2013-14, (c) 2012-13, (d) 2011-12 and (e) 2010-11.","false","Biography information for Dame Margaret Hodge","Barking","Margaret Hodge","3019"
