"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381858","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-23","<p /> <p>The information requested in all four questions above is published and available at:</p><p><a href="https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/" target="_blank">https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk</a></p><p>Guidance on how to extract the information required can be found at:</p><p><a href="https://sw.stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/webapi/online-help/Getting-Started---SuperWEB2.html" target="_blank">https://sw.stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/webapi/online-help/Getting-Started---SuperWEB2.html</a></p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","3015 ; 3021 ; 3025","2015-06-23T15:35:01.327Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381858/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381858/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381858/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-17","Social Rented Housing: Barking and Dagenham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many social housing tenants are under the age of 65 in the London Borough of Barking and Dagenham.","false","Biography information for Dame Margaret Hodge","Barking","Margaret Hodge","2969"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381859","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-06-25","<p>Two Libyan nationals formerly based at Bassingbourn barracks are currently serving in prison establishments in England and Wales. Neither will be released within the next six months. Three further Libyan nationals, formerly based at Bassingbourn barracks, are held in immigration detention. <br></p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2015-06-25T16:06:24.487Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381859/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381859/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381859/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-06-17","Prisoners: Libya","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many Libyans formerly based at Bassingbourn barracks (a) are in prison in the UK and (b) it is expected will be released from prison having completed their sentences within the next six months; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","2866"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381860","Home Office","false","2015-06-25","<p>The general policy of the Home Office is not to disclose personal information about another person. This is because we have obligations under the Data Protection Act and in law generally to protect this information.</p><p>The UK has a proud history of granting asylum to those who need our protection and every claim will be considered on its individual merits.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2015-06-25T15:42:19.427Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381860/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381860/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381860/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-06-17","Asylum: Libya","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many Libyans formerly based at Bassingbourn barracks remain in the UK having claimed asylum; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","2867"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381861","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-24","<p>The current cost of the repairs caused by the Libyans is approximately £138,000 which is being recovered from the Libyan Government.</p><p>This amount covers replacement to fixtures and fittings and the repair/replacement of fire detection and alarm systems.</p><p>Repairs are currently ongoing.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-06-24T16:08:04.63Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381861/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381861/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381861/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-17","Military bases: Bassingbourn","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what damage to Bassingbourn base was caused by Libyan soldiers on their training mission at the base; what the cost of repairs arising from that damage was; whether all such repairs are now completed; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","2850"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381862","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-23","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 11 June 2015 to Question 1095. Ministry of Defence (MOD) commercial officers are also aware of two contracts relating to training with respect to conflict zones. These were for interpreter services firstly in support of UK training in the Ukraine and secondly for the selection in Tripoli and training at Bassingbourn of Libyan soldiers. More broadly, information on MOD contracts is not recorded in a way that would allow an automatic search to identify those relating to conflict zones, or to training. A manual search would incur disproportionate cost.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2015-06-23T16:26:45.453Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381862/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381862/answer","20150611_1095_Iraq_Military_Aid.doc","20150611_1095_Iraq_Military_Aid.doc","20150611 - QnA extract on Iraq: Military Aid","20150611 - QnA extract on Iraq: Military Aid","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381862/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-17","Military Aid: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 11 June 2015 to Question 1095, how many contracts to provide any form of military training in conflict zones were awarded to (a) private security companies and (b) other companies in each of the last five years; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","2852"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381863","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-24","<p>Before the base closed in 2012 there were a number of facilities available at the site, including an Astroturf pitch, golf course, dry ski slope and open space for recreational pursuits, which created approximately £30,000 per annum. The Tower Museum is also located at Bassingbourn.</p><p>No clubs currently use the site.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-06-24T16:09:41.96Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381863/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381863/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381863/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-17","Military Bases: Bassingbourn","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what facilities at Bassingbourn base (a) have been and (b) are being made available to the local community; what estimate he has made of the value of provision of those facilities; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","2853"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381864","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-24","<p>No new investment was made at Bassingbourn Barracks in the period between 1 April 2010 and the handover of the Barracks to the Defence Infrastructure Organisation in January 2013.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-06-24T16:06:04.83Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381864/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381864/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381864/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-17","Military Bases: Bassingbourn","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what improvements were made to Bassingbourn base in each year since 2010; what the cost was of each such improvement; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","2855"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381865","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-23","<p>The contract for the manufacturing phase of the Scout Specialist Vehicle (SV) programme was awarded to General Dynamics UK Limited (GD UK) in September 2014. GD UK, as the prime contractor, is responsible for the selection and management of its supply chain. Its detailed breakdown of GD UK's subcontractors, including contract values and end dates, is commercially sensitive and not held by the Department. The supply chain for the acquisition of the Scout SV includes countries from across the globe, but over 60% of the contract value is based in the UK, including 160 UK based companies.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-06-23T16:23:19.047Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381865/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381865/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381865/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-17","Armoured Fighting Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 8 June 2015, to Question 1093, which companies hold contracts for the building of the remaining Scout Specialist vehicles; what the value of each such contract is; when he expects the contracts for those vehicles to end; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","2857"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381866","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-23","<p>A company's 'classification' is neither considered nor detailed as part of the procurement process and therefore would not be changed. The suitability of companies in other respects (eg legal and financial compliance) is considered before a contract is let.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2015-06-23T16:25:37.697Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381866/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381866/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381866/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-17","Military Aid: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 11 June 2015, to Question 1095, how many times the classification of private security companies contracted to provide services in conflict zones was changed to training companies in each year since 2010; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","2858"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381867","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-24","<p>As of 22 June 2015, 26 service complaints have been raised by serving or former members of the Armed Forces - seven from the Royal Navy, 18 from the Army, and one from the Royal Air Force. Of the total, 21 were submitted in response to letters, and five were submitted prior to the letters being sent out.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-06-24T15:31:06.063Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381867/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381867/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381867/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-17","Armed Forces: Complaints","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 8 June 2015 to Question 1366, how many personnel from each branch of the armed forces have made a complaint; how many such personnel have responded to (a) letters sent to their last address and (b) information on his Department's website; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","2897"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381868","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-23","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 2 June 2015 to Question 207.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2015-06-23T16:24:12.837Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381868/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381868/answer","Hansard Extract 2 June 2015 HOC 2876.doc","Hansard Extract 2 June 2015 HOC 2876.doc","Ministry of Defence: Private Military and Security","Ministry of Defence: Private Military and Security","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381868/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-17","Afghanistan and Iraq: Private Military and Security Companies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 3 June 2015 to Question 337, how many private companies were employed by his Department in (a) Iraq and (b) Afghanistan in each of the last five years; what services each such company provided; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","2876"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381869","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-24","<p>The Department does not hold any correspondence between Public Health England (PHE) and the Ministry of Defence (MOD) in relation to hallucinations, psychosis or suicidal thoughts in personnel prescribed Mefloquine (commercial name Lariam).</p><p>The use of Mefloquine by the MOD is based on the expert guidance of the PHE Advisory Committee on Malaria Prevention on which the MOD has a representative.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-06-24T15:34:40.947Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381869/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381869/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381869/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-17","Armed Forces: Mefloquine","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 1 June 2015 to Question 126, when he plans to place in the Library the correspondence between 2010 and 2015 between his Department and Public Health England in relation to use of Lariam or Mefloquine and reports of (a) hallucinations, (b) psychosis and (c) suicidal thoughts in personnel prescribed those medications.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","2877"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381870","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-06-23","<p>The Government mechanisms for incentivising deployment of renewable electricity are generation-based. This means that support is granted on the basis of each megawatt-hour of electricity actually generated by stations which qualify for accreditation under a scheme or which secure a contract for difference (CfD) to provide support. No scheme offers financial support for the development of generating stations.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-06-23T14:54:23.78Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381870/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381870/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381870/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-06-17","Solar Power: Bridgend","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, whether Government funding or subsidy has been offered or promised to Suncredit UK Ltd to develop a solar park at Court Colman, Bridgend; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","2851"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381871","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-22","<p /> <p>Estimates of the UK disability employment rate can be found on the Office for National Statistics website at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.ons.gov.uk/ons/rel/lms/labour-market-statistics/may-2015/table-a08.xls" target="_blank">http://www.ons.gov.uk/ons/rel/lms/labour-market-statistics/may-2015/table-a08.xls</a></p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-06-22T16:00:22.89Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381871/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381871/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381871/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-17","Employment: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate he has made of changes in the rate of disability employment in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Sir Oliver Heald","North East Hertfordshire","Sir Oliver Heald","2887"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381872","Department of Health","false","2015-06-26","<p>We have made reducing stillbirth an improvement area for the National Health Service in the NHS Outcomes Framework. It is encouraging that the stillbirth rate in England has fallen from 5.2 stillbirths per 1,000 total births in 2011 to 4.7 in 2013.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Department is working with key partners, including NHS England, Public Health England, Royal College of Obstetricians and Gynaecologists, Royal College of Midwives and the stillbirth and neonatal death charity Sands, to identify and drive forward the actions required to help reduce further the stillbirth and neonatal mortality rate in England.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Our stillbirth prevention work programme aims to reduce stillbirth and neonatal mortality by raising awareness of the known risk factors; identifying the currently unknown factors and causes associated with perinatal and infant mortality; and facilitate the learning and sharing of good practice across the NHS.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>This programme covers a range of initiatives which include raising awareness of the known risk factors among pregnant women and health professionals. This will ensure women receive consistent advice on how to minimise the risk of stillbirth – including the importance of eating healthily and not smoking or drinking alcohol – as well as being aware of fetal movement and what is normal for their baby, and where to go for help if they suspect there is a problem.</p><p> </p><p>Reducing perinatal mortality, including stillbirth, is included as an improvement area for the NHS in the NHS Outcomes Framework and remains a priority for the Government.</p><p> </p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer",,"2015-06-26T11:54:44.247Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381872/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381872/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381872/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-17","Perinatal Mortality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps his Department is taking to reduce the number of stillbirths.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","2934"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381873","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-06-22","<p>The Government is currently considering the full implications of the decision of the European Court of Justice on the application of the VAT reduced rate to the installation of energy saving materials.</p><p>Estimates based on provisional internal analysis suggest that around 1.5% fewer households would meet the Green Deal’s Golden Rule if the VAT rate was 20% instead of 5%.</p><p>In England, most Energy Company Obligation (ECO) delivery does not involve blending with private finance or other funding streams, so there is likely to be minimal impact were there to be a VAT increase.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-06-22T10:06:29.513Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381873/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381873/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381873/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-06-17","Energy: Conservation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, with reference to the ruling of the European Court of Justice on 4 June 2015 on the UK's VAT rate on the supply and installation of energy-saving materials, what assessment she has made of (a) the implications for her policies of that ruling and (b) the effect that ruling will have on measures to improve energy efficiency.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","2998"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381874","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-06-22","<p>There is currently no methodology to enable an estimate to be made of the number of social housing tenants who do not meet the qualification requirements for the Warm Home Discount Scheme. However, during the four years of the scheme we have not received representations to suggest that social tenants have been disproportionately unable to access the scheme.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-06-22T10:08:22.957Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381874/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381874/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381874/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-06-17","Warm Home Discount Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, pursuant to the Answer of 16 June 2015 to Question 2098, what estimate she has made of the number of social housing tenants who will not be eligible for inclusion in the Warm Home Discount scheme.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","2999"
