"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381959","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-23","<p /> <p>The latest available information on sanctions, up to December 2014, is published at:</p><p><a href="https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/" target="_blank">https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/</a>:</p><p> </p><p>Guidance on how to extract the information required can be found at:</p><p><a href="https://sw.stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/webapi/online-help/Getting-Started---SuperWEB2.html" target="_blank">https://sw.stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/webapi/online-help/Getting-Started---SuperWEB2.html</a></p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-06-23T14:24:34.777Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381959/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381959/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381959/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-17","Social Security Benefits: Aberdeen","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people had their benefits sanctioned in Aberdeen in each of the last 12 quarters for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Kirsty Blackman","Aberdeen North","Kirsty Blackman","2950"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381960","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-24","<p /> <p>This information is not available.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-06-24T14:15:33.417Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381960/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381960/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381960/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-17","Social Security Benefits: Brighton and Hove","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will estimate the proportion of families in Brighton and Hove in households subject to the benefit cap who would not be able to afford average housing costs in that local authority area if the cap were set at £23,000 per year; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","2870"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381961","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-23","<p /> <p>It is estimated around 86% of broad market rental areas in Great Britain are currently affordable for a single parent with three children and three bedrooms who are subject to the benefit cap at £26,000 per year. Affordability for (a) a couple with children and (c) other families in households subject to the benefit cap would depend on the number of children and the number of bedrooms the household has.</p><p> </p><p>No households are subject to a £23,000 benefit cap.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-06-23T15:18:25.05Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381961/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381961/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381961/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-17","Private Rented Housing: Rents","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will estimate in what proportion of broad market rental areas (a) a couple with children, (b) a single parent with three children and three bedrooms and (c) other families in households subject to the benefit cap at (i) £26,000 and (ii) £23,000 per year can afford average private sector rent.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","2869"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381962","Prime Minister","false","2015-06-22","<p>As I explained in my letter to Sir John, I have asked the Cabinet Secretary to meet him as soon as possible to discuss progress for completion of the report and ways in which the Civil Service can assist the Inquiry in the urgent completion of its work.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron",,"2015-06-22T15:29:54.087Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381962/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381962/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381962/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2015-06-17","Iraq Committee of Inquiry","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, with reference to his letter to Sir John Chilcot of 17 June 2015, if he will instruct the Cabinet Secretary to discuss with Sir John at the proposed meeting the imposition of an urgent deadline for the receipt of responses from individuals contacted as part of the Maxwellisation process.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","2933"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381963","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-06-26","<p>This Government is committed to providing language service professionals who meet the needs of those requiring support in the justice system, including those working with deaf and deafblind people.</p><p> </p><p>Future provision of the service is currently being explored.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2015-06-26T13:59:15.3Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381963/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381963/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381963/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-06-17","Ministry of Justice: Interpreters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether his Department's second generation contract for the supply of language services will require interpreters to be registered with the National Registers of Communications Professionals Working with Deaf and Deafblind People or the National Register of Public Service Interpreters.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","2854"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381964","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-23","<p /> <p>The Government does not collect data on total numbers of people unable to afford a low-cost funeral.</p><p> </p><p>The Social Fund Funeral Expenses Payment scheme provides help towards funeral costs. In 2013/14 over 33,000 awards were made to people in Great Britain. These payments were worth £44.7 million with an average award of £1,347. Social Fund Budgeting Loans are also available to help those on income related benefits to cover the costs relating to funeral expenses.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-06-23T14:30:43.19Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381964/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381964/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381964/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-17","Funerals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will estimate the number of people who are unable to afford a low-cost funeral; and what steps his Department is taking to assist such people with funeral costs.","false","Biography information for Ronnie Cowan","Inverclyde","Ronnie Cowan","2971"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381965","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-22","<p>The information as requested is not available and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-06-22T14:22:42.997Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381965/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381965/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381965/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-17","Social Security Benefits: Disqualification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what information his Department holds on the ages of children whose parents have been subject to welfare benefits sanctions.","false","Biography information for Anne McLaughlin","Glasgow North East","Anne McLaughlin","3000"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381966","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-06-22","<p>Information on the proportion of employers offering apprenticeships is not centrally collected. However, data from the 2014 UKCES Employer Perspectives Survey[1] show that 16 per cent of all employers in the UK offered apprenticeships. The majority of these (15% of all employers) were formal Apprenticeships.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Among those employers offering formal Apprenticeships in the UK, 74 per cent offered them to 16 to 18 year olds and 75 per cent offered them to 19 to 24 year olds. Data is not available for the 16 to 19 age group or at regional or constituency levels.</p><p> </p><br /><p>[1]<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/373769/14.11.11._EPS_2014_-_Main_Report_full_V2.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/373769/14.11.11._EPS_2014_-_Main_Report_full_V2.pdf</a> (p.90)</p><p> </p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2015-06-22T13:51:07.413Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381966/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381966/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381966/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-06-17","Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what proportion of employers offer apprenticeships to 16 to 19 year olds in (a) the UK, (b) the North East and (c) Berwick-upon-Tweed constituency.","false","Biography information for Anne-Marie Trevelyan","Berwick-upon-Tweed","Mrs Anne-Marie Trevelyan","2878"
