"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381970","Department of Health","false","2015-06-25","<p>The data on waiting times to see a general practitioner is not held centrally.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The information for the average waiting time for referral to secondary care in England and Enfield Clinical Commissioning Group (that covers Edmonton) is shown in the following table.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Average (median) waiting times in weeks from referral to treatment<sup>1</sup>, April 2015</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>Patients who were admitted to</p><p>hospital during the month</p></td><td><p>Patients who were not admitted</p><p>to hospital (e.g. outpatients)</p><p>during the month</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>NHS Enfield Clinical</p><p>Commissioning Group</p></td><td><p>8.3</p></td><td><p>6.6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>England</p></td><td><p>9.0</p></td><td><p>5.5</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p><em> </em></p><p> </p><p><em>Source:</em> Consultant-led referral to treatment waiting times, NHS England</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><em>Note: </em>The NHS Constitution sets out the right for patients to start consultant-led treatment within a maximum of 18 weeks from referral for non-urgent conditions.</p><p> </p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2015-06-25T16:07:47.677Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381970/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381970/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381970/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-17","General Practitioners: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the average waiting time for a GP appointment is; and what the average waiting time is for referral to secondary care in (a) Edmonton and (b) England.","false","Biography information for Kate Osamor","Edmonton","Kate Osamor","2941"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381971","Home Office","false","2015-06-23","<p>The Home Office does not collect this information centrally. The Home Office collates information recorded by police forces on the age, ethnicity and gender of people arrested on suspicion of a criminal offence, but not specifically in relation to mental ill health. Last October the Home Secretary announced plans to work with forces to pilot the collection of data on people detained under section 135 and 136 of the Mental Health Act. This will capture the age, ethnicity, and gender of people detained, as well as the place of safety used, including the use of police cells. The initiative is voluntary in 2015/16 with a view to it becoming a mandatory part of the Home Office’s Annual Data Requirement for all forces in England and Wales from 2016/17. National figures will be based on aggregated data and it will not be possible to provide a detailed breakdown of the age, ethnicity or gender of those people taken to police custody as opposed to another place of safety.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2015-06-23T15:37:37.477Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381971/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381971/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381971/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-06-17","Police Custody: Mental Illness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether her Department collects information on the age, ethnicity and gender of people with mental illnesses detained in police custody.","false","Biography information for Kate Osamor","Edmonton","Kate Osamor","3034"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381972","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-22","<p>It is important to consider tax and public spending decisions alongside welfare decisions, to understand the cumulative impact on households of government policy.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Details of the impact on households as a result of changes to tax, welfare and public service spending can be found in the Treasury’s distributional analysis publication that accompanied Budget 2015.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Unlike other analyses, it looks not only at the effect of direct tax and welfare decisions, but also the impact of changes to indirect tax (such as the freeze to fuel duty) and changes to spending on public services.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>This analysis can be found at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/budget-2015-documents" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/budget-2015-documents</a></p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-06-22T16:31:19.73Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381972/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381972/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381972/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-17","Welfare State: Reform","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the effect on household incomes of the welfare changes introduced since May 2010 as a proportion of household income for each income decile.","false","Biography information for Angela Crawley","Lanark and Hamilton East","Angela Crawley","2840"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381973","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-06-22","<p> </p><p /> <p>Since December 2013, three of the five currently approved neonicotinoids have not been permitted for use on a wide range of crops considered “attractive to bees”. A number of other uses remain permitted under the EU approval.</p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p>The Government has implemented these restrictions in full. The European Commission has begun a review of the science relating to the restrictions. The Government believes that decisions should be made on the basis of the scientific evidence and will fully participate in this review.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2015-06-22T14:41:27.917Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381973/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381973/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381973/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-17","Neonicotinoids: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what her Department's position is on an EU-wide ban on neonicotinoid pesticides.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","3044"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381974","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-06-22","<p>Decisions on the approval of pesticide active substances are made at EU level. In late 2013, the EU imposed restrictions on three neonicotinoids that are “attractive to bees”. The UK has implemented these rules in full. The European Commission has begun a review of the science relating to the restrictions. The government believes that decisions should be made on the basis of the scientific evidence and will fully participate in this review.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Growers’ representatives have made it clear that they regard the restrictions as problematic for the production of affected crops. They are not convinced that the evidence suggests that bees are harmed from use of these pesticides.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2015-06-22T14:47:33.02Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381974/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381974/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381974/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-17","Neonicotinoids: EU law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what representations her Department has received from the UK grower community on repeal of the ban on the use of neonicotinoid pesticides.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","3045"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381975","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-06-22","<p>Local newspapers are an important source of information for local communities and a vital part of a healthy democracy. For this reason, the government will consult in due course on whether to introduce a business rates relief for local newspapers in England to support them as they adapt to new technology and changing circumstances.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-06-22T16:04:32.897Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381975/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381975/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381975/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-06-17","Local Press","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment his Department has made of the adequacy of government support for local newspapers; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","2957"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381976","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-22","<p>Local newspapers are an important source of information for local communities and a vital part of a healthy democracy. We are committed to consulting on the introduction of a business rates relief to support local newspapers in England as they adapt to new technology and changing circumstances.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-06-22T16:26:56.02Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381976/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381976/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381976/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-17","Non-domestic Rates: Local Press","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether he plans to bring forward legislative proposals to amend the level of business rates for local newspapers; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","2958"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381977","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-22","<p>Royal Navy ships routinely operate with NATO partners including US forces; this may involve the embarkation of US Marines on Royal Navy ships. We expect approximately 40 US Marines will join Royal Marines embarking on HMS OCEAN as part of a proposed exercise later this year.</p><p>The US Marines would not be part of NATO's quick-reaction forces.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","2912","2015-06-22T15:42:55.17Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381977/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381977/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381977/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-17","HMS Ocean","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, on what date US marines are planned to be deployed on HMS Ocean as part of NATO quick-reaction forces.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","2911"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381978","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-22","<p>Royal Navy ships routinely operate with NATO partners including US forces; this may involve the embarkation of US Marines on Royal Navy ships. We expect approximately 40 US Marines will join Royal Marines embarking on HMS OCEAN as part of a proposed exercise later this year.</p><p>The US Marines would not be part of NATO's quick-reaction forces.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","2911","2015-06-22T15:42:55.277Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381978/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381978/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381978/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-17","HMS Ocean","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many US marines are planned to be deployed on HMS Ocean as part of NATO quick-reaction forces.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","2912"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381979","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-22","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 9 June to Question 1245.</p><p>We are working through the further detail of the announcement.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon","3007","2015-06-22T15:42:14.157Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381979/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381979/answer","Hansard Extract Tuesday 9 June 2015.doc","Hansard Extract Tuesday 9 June 2015.doc","Armed Forces: Disciplinary Proceedings","Armed Forces: Disciplinary Proceedings","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381979/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-17","Ministry of Defence: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 15 June 2015 to Question 1818, how much expenditure will be reduced on (a) consultants, (b) overtime and travel and (c) re-profiting of equipment and infrastructure spend in 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","3008"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381980","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-22","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 9 June to Question 1245.</p><p>We are working through the further detail of the announcement.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon","3008","2015-06-22T15:42:14.057Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381980/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381980/answer","Hansard Extract Tuesday 9 June 2015.doc","Hansard Extract Tuesday 9 June 2015.doc","Armed Forces: Disciplinary Proceedings","Armed Forces: Disciplinary Proceedings","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381980/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-17","Ministry of Defence: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 15 June 2015 to Question 1818, what equipment and infrastructure spending will be re-profiled in order to meet the £500 million reduction in his Department's budget for 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","3007"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381981","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-22","<p>Train Operating Companies are responsible for the timetabling of passenger services. Passengers can expect circa 15 minute journey time improvements on the Great Western (GWML) and East Coast (ECML) routes into Paddington and King’s Cross, along with increased frequencies of trains which I expect to be achieved from both fleets.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In addition, the 9-car trainsets on the ECML have 18% more seats than the InterCity 225 trains that they are replacing. The programme will increase the number of seats in the morning peak in to Kings Cross (ECML) by 28%, and by 40% in to Paddington (GWML).</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2015-06-22T12:58:46.893Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381981/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381981/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381981/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-17","Rolling Stock: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 17 June 2015 to Question 2340, on which journeys on which lines passengers can expect a 15 minute journey time improvement as a result of the introduction of (a) bi-mode IEP and (b) electric IEP trains.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","3011"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381982","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-22","<p>The report “HS2 Direct Connections Study” is being considered as part of the East Midlands Councils’ response to the Phase Two consultation that ran from July 2013 to January 2014. No decisions on the Phase Two route and station locations have been made. The Government intends to announce the way forward on Phase Two later this year.</p><p> </p><p>We welcome partnerships such as Midlands Connect that are looking to maximise the economic potential of the Midlands and to make the most of HS2.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-06-22T12:56:43.047Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381982/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381982/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381982/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-17","High Speed 2 Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the implications for his policies of the findings in the report entitled, HS2 Direct Connections Study, published by East Midlands Council on 18 December 2013; and if he will take steps to support the Midlands Connect initiative.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","3010"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381983","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-22","<p>Following our agreement in principle last November to devolve executive rail franchising functions to the Welsh Government, decisions on the procurement and management of the next Wales and Border franchise from October 2018, including rolling stock, will be for the Welsh Government.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The electrification programme on Great Western will see the introduction of electric trains that will facilitate the displacement of pacer trains by higher quality diesel rolling stock.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2015-06-22T09:53:48.89Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381983/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381983/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381983/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-17","Great Western Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether he plans to withdraw Pacer trains from the Great Western and Wales and Borders franchises.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","3009"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381984","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-22","<p>Whilst the Department is aware that proposals for dealing with the results of the 2013 valuation of a number of sections within the Railways Pension Scheme have been approved by the Trustee, we do not have details of the specific sections involved.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2015-06-22T10:58:38.713Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381984/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381984/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381984/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-17","Railways: Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 9 June 2015 to Question 1549, whether proposals for the Atos and Atos Worldline sections of the Railway Pension Scheme have been approved by the Trustee.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","3006"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384790","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-06-23","<p>On 11 June we announced the start of the post-implementation review of the introduction of fees in the Employment Tribunal. The review will consider how successful the policy has been in achieving its original objectives, which included maintaining access to justice for those seeking to bring disputes to the Tribunal. Our intention is to complete the review later this year.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2015-06-23T15:15:52.353Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384790/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384790/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384790/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-06-17","Employment Tribunals Service: Fees and Charges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, if he will review the level of employment tribunal fees.","false","Biography information for Anne McLaughlin","Glasgow North East","Anne McLaughlin","900502"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384791","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-06-23","<p /> <p>Maintaining family links, education and promoting aspiration are essential to helping female offenders turn their lives around. The women’s custodial estate has been reconfigured so that women offenders can be held as close as possible to their homes, with access to the right interventions and opportunities for meaningful resettlement.</p><p> </p><p>In addition, Community Rehabilitation Companies are providing embedded resettlement services, which are required to be tailored to the specific needs of women.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2015-06-23T15:26:52.437Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384791/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384791/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384791/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-06-17","Prisoners: Rehabilitation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what steps he plans to take to increase the effectiveness of rehabilitation of female prisoners.","false","Biography information for Mrs Heather Wheeler","South Derbyshire","Heather Wheeler","900507"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384792","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-06-23","<p>The Government was elected with a mandate to reform and modernise the UK human rights framework. The UK has a proud tradition of respect for human rights which long pre-dates the 1998 Human Rights Act. But the 1998 Act opened the system to abuse, which has damaged the credibility of human rights.</p><p> </p><p>We will bring forward proposals for a British Bill of Rights, which will replace the Human Rights Act. Our Bill will protect fundamental human rights, but also prevent their abuse and restore common sense to the system.</p><p> </p><p>The Queen’s Speech included a clear commitment to bring forward proposals for a Bill of Rights in this parliamentary session. We will then legislate after full consultation.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2015-06-23T15:20:43.137Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384792/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384792/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384792/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-06-17","Bill of Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what progress he has made on his plans for a British Bill of Rights; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Alan Mak","Havant","Mr Alan Mak","900504"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384793","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-06-23","<p /> <p>The Government's reform programme is intended to deliver a simpler justice system that is more accessible to the public. Changes in scope for Legal Aid protect funding for those who really need legal advice.</p><p> </p><p>Our reforms also aim to support people in resolving their disputes by means of more informal and less costly remedies than going to court.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2015-06-23T15:10:26.017Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384793/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384793/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384793/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-06-17","Administration of Justice","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what steps he plans to take to ensure access to justice regardless of ability to pay.","false","Biography information for Carolyn Harris","Swansea East","Carolyn Harris","900503"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381343","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-06-23","<p>Energy-intensive industries already participate in National Grid’s balancing services reducing their consumption at times of high demand. These contracts are on a voluntary, bilateral, and commercial basis.</p><p>Government has committed to two years of ‘Transitional Arrangements’ before the full Capacity Market begins, aimed to support new demand side providers including these industries, to grow and prepare prior to the first year ahead auction in 2017.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-06-23T14:34:06.987Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381343/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381343/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381343/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-06-16","Energy Intensive Industries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what steps her Department has taken to assist energy-intensive industries in preparing contingency plans for requests to reduce their demand for electricity at times of system stress; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for David T. C. Davies","Monmouth","David T. C. Davies","2753"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381345","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-06-22","<p>The fees paid or to be paid to the firms involved in the recent sale of Royal Mail shares by the Government do not include a discretionary element.</p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-06-22T13:33:02.6Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381345/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381345/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381345/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-06-16","Royal Mail","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, pursuant to the Answer of 16 June 2015 to Question 1839, what discretionary fees and payments (a) have been and (b) will be made to each of those firms.","false","Biography information for Chuka Umunna","Streatham","Mr Chuka Umunna","2810"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381347","Cabinet Office","false","2015-06-22","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p><p> </p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson",,"2015-06-22T16:10:59.133Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381347/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381347/answer","PQ 2807 Haigh MP.pdf","PQ 2807 Haigh MP.pdf","UKSA Letter to Member - Death from Influenza","UKSA Letter to Member - Death from Influenza","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381347/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-06-16","Influenza: Death","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many people died from influenza in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","2807"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381348","Cabinet Office","false","2015-06-22","<p>There is no formal requirement for public bodies to offer responses to public correspondence and inquiries made in the Gaelic language in that language.</p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2015-06-22T16:08:02.1Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381348/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381348/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381348/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-06-16","Public Bodies: Scots Gaelic Language","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what requirements there are for public bodies with reserved functions to offer responses to public correspondence and inquiries made in the Gaelic language in that language; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Alison Thewliss","Glasgow Central","Alison Thewliss","2824"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381349","Cabinet Office","false","2015-06-22","<p>The matching of electoral registers against Government and local authority data, referred to as ‘confirmation,’ was a one off exercise to help simplify the change to Individual Electoral Registration (IER). It resulted in 87% of existing electors being automatically transferred to the new registers under IER without needing to take any action. Data matching continues to form an important part of the system for voter registration, in verifying new applications, but also locally in identifying and verifying applications from eligible electors. We will keep under review the scope for data to further improve voter registration.</p>","Weston-super-Mare","John Penrose",,"2015-06-22T16:18:37.053Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381349/answer","Biography information for John Penrose","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381349/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381349/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-06-16","Electoral Register","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what consideration the Government has given to continuing to use the matching system between the electoral register and Government databases that was used in the transition towards Individual Electoral Registration.","false","Biography information for Emma Reynolds","Wolverhampton North East","Emma Reynolds","2641"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381350","Cabinet Office","false","2015-06-22","<p>The Electoral Commission published their analysis of the electoral registers used for the elections on 7 May 2015. The full report can be found at:</p><p><a href="http://www.electoralcommission.org.uk/__data/assets/pdf_file/0006/190464/IER-June-report.pdf" target="_blank">http://www.electoralcommission.org.uk/__data/assets/pdf_file/0006/190464/IER-June-report.pdf</a></p>","Weston-super-Mare","John Penrose",,"2015-06-22T16:21:21.48Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381350/answer","Biography information for John Penrose","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381350/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381350/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-06-16","Electoral Register","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what assessment he has made of the effect on the number of people on the electoral register of the transition to Individual Electoral Registration.","false","Biography information for Emma Reynolds","Wolverhampton North East","Emma Reynolds","2651"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381351","Cabinet Office","false","2015-06-22","<p>The Cabinet Office published results in November 2014 of the nationwide data matching process referred to as ‘confirmation’ between government records and local data with electoral registers during the transition to Individual Electoral Registration.</p><p>The report is available at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/using-data-matching-to-confirm-electors-in-great-britain" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/using-data-matching-to-confirm-electors-in-great-britain</a></p>","Weston-super-Mare","John Penrose","2653","2015-06-22T16:23:23.77Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381351/answer","Biography information for John Penrose","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381351/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381351/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-06-16","Electoral Register","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what assessment he has made of the effectiveness of the (a) national and (b) local match system used in the transition to Individual Electoral Registration.","false","Biography information for Emma Reynolds","Wolverhampton North East","Emma Reynolds","2652"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381352","Cabinet Office","false","2015-06-22","<p>The Cabinet Office published results in November 2014 of the nationwide data matching process referred to as ‘confirmation’ between government records and local data with electoral registers during the transition to Individual Electoral Registration.</p><p>The report is available at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/using-data-matching-to-confirm-electors-in-great-britain" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/using-data-matching-to-confirm-electors-in-great-britain</a></p>","Weston-super-Mare","John Penrose","2652","2015-06-22T16:23:23.87Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381352/answer","Biography information for John Penrose","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381352/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381352/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-06-16","Electoral Register","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what (a) national and (b) local match rates between the electoral register and government databases were used in the transition towards Individual Electoral Registration (i) overall and (ii) in each local authority and parliamentary constituency.","false","Biography information for Emma Reynolds","Wolverhampton North East","Emma Reynolds","2653"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381353","Cabinet Office","false","2015-06-22","<p>Deposits are not currently required for candidates to stand in local government elections and the Government does not have any plans to introduce such a provision.</p>","Weston-super-Mare","John Penrose",,"2015-06-22T16:27:00.72Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381353/answer","Biography information for John Penrose","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381353/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381353/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-06-16","Elections","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, if he will bring forward legislative proposals to increase the deposit necessary to stand in local elections.","false","Biography information for Simon Danczuk","Rochdale","Simon Danczuk","2654"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381355","Cabinet Office","false","2015-06-23","<p>The Government has no plans to change the current arrangements in this area.</p>","Weston-super-Mare","John Penrose",,"2015-06-23T15:56:49.463Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381355/answer","Biography information for John Penrose","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381355/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381355/answer","Weston-super-Mare","John Penrose","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381355/answer/previousversion/7533","Biography information for John Penrose","53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-06-16","Elections","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, if he will bring forward legislative proposals to prevent candidates standing in both local and general elections when those elections are held on the same day.","false","Biography information for Simon Danczuk","Rochdale","Simon Danczuk","2655"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381356","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-23","<p>Detailed geographical information within local authority areas for the 2012-13 tax year detailing the number of families in receipt of tax credits in Wales can be found on gov.uk: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/personal-tax-credits-finalised-award-statistics-small-area-data-lsoa-and-data-zone-201213" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/personal-tax-credits-finalised-award-statistics-small-area-data-lsoa-and-data-zone-201213</a>. <br></p><p> </p><p>Information relating to people qualifying for working tax credits in each constituency in North Wales is not available.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","2647","2015-06-23T13:10:13.787Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381356/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381356/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381356/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-16","Welfare Tax Credits: North Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the 100 local authority wards are in North Wales with the highest number of people receiving tax credits.","false","Biography information for Mark Tami","Alyn and Deeside","Mark Tami","2648"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381357","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-23","<p>Detailed geographical information within local authority areas for the 2012-13 tax year detailing the number of families in receipt of tax credits in Wales can be found on gov.uk: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/personal-tax-credits-finalised-award-statistics-small-area-data-lsoa-and-data-zone-201213" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/personal-tax-credits-finalised-award-statistics-small-area-data-lsoa-and-data-zone-201213</a>. <br></p><p> </p><p>Information relating to people qualifying for working tax credits in each constituency in North Wales is not available.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","2648","2015-06-23T13:10:13.663Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381357/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381357/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381357/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-16","Working Tax Credit: North Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many people qualify for working tax credit in each constituency in North Wales.","false","Biography information for Mark Tami","Alyn and Deeside","Mark Tami","2647"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381358","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-22","<p>The Treasury and HM Revenue and Customs published research analysing the dynamic effects of fuel duty reductions in a joint report in April 2014. This research can be found here: https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/analysis-of-the-dynamic-effects-of-fuel-duty-reductions</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2015-06-22T14:25:08.937Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381358/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381358/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381358/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-16","Fuels: Excise Duties","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what research he has conducted to inform the setting of the level of fuel duty.","false","Biography information for Barry Gardiner","Brent North","Barry Gardiner","2612"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381359","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-22","<p>Ministers are not privy to the details of the tax affairs of individual companies.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) are legally obliged to protect taxpayer confidentiality.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-06-22T16:00:04.363Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381359/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381359/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381359/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-16","London Airports: Corporation Tax","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much corporation tax Heathrow and Gatwick Airports paid in each of the last five years; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","2632"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381360","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-23","<p>Registering for Tax-Free Childcare will be straightforward for parents. Using a simple online system, parents will be asked to identify themselves and the child for whom the childcare account is being opened. In most cases, this information will be processed and checked automatically.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In a minority of cases, HMRC may need to check the child’s birth certificate. This process will be as efficient as possible to minimise any delay in the parent opening a childcare account.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2015-06-23T13:35:34.28Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381360/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381360/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381360/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-16","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the expected time taken will be for people to register for tax free childcare as a result of being required to send their children's birth certificate to HM Revenue and Customs.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","2608"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381361","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-22","<p>The Government announced at Autumn Statement 2013 that it would make a £30 million contribution to the costs of the Garden Bridge, which was matched by a further £30 million contribution by Transport for London. The Garden Bridge Trust, which is promoting and delivering the project, says that the delivery costs are expected to be within £175 million in addition to ongoing costs of £3.5 million annually.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2015-06-22T16:32:48.933Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381361/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381361/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381361/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-16","Garden Bridge","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much the Government (a) has spent and (b) plans to spend on the proposed London Garden Bridge; and what information his Department holds on the total cost of that project.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Turner","Isle of Wight","Mr Andrew Turner","2661"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381362","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-23","<p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) provides a wide range of guidance for all businesses on VAT legislation and their tax obligations at:</p><p> </p><p>www.gov.uk/business-tax/vat</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>This includes guidance on VAT simplification schemes for small businesses.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>HMRC provides additional guidance and support through VAT webinars specifically tailored to meet the needs of small businesses. These cover key areas such as VAT registration, how to keep business records, what to charge VAT on and how and when to pay VAT to HMRC.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>VAT webinars are delivered live, where attendees have the opportunity to ask HMRC Business Advisors questions, and are also available online as recorded versions so businesses can access them at any time and are supported by downloadable frequently asked questions.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-06-23T16:06:55.2Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381362/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381362/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381362/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-16","VAT","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what guidance he has issued to small businesses on adherence to VAT legislation.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","2674"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381363","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-06-22","<p>Fuel poverty is a devolved matter.</p><p>In England, the Government is fully committed to tackling fuel poverty, including meeting a new 2030 target now enshrined in law. Official statistics show that fuel poverty has fallen in England every year since 2010, demonstrating that the Government’s policies are working. Flagship policies such as the Energy Company Obligation and Warm Home Discount (both of which operate across Great Britain) help millions of low income and vulnerable households each year with heating and insulation measures as well as direct reductions in their energy bills.</p><p>The Northern Ireland Executive decides its own fuel poverty objectives and policies. For example, the Department for Social Development offers energy efficiency improvement schemes for low income households through the Warm Homes Scheme, Boiler Replacement Scheme and the Affordable Warmth Scheme.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-06-22T10:09:40.92Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381363/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381363/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381363/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-06-16","Fuel Poverty","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what steps she has taken to reduce fuel poverty.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","2675"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381364","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-24","<p>Records show that a filling station in the KW12 postcode area submitted evidence as part of the Calls for Information in September 2013. The filling station submitted the price spreadsheet provided here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/proposed-extension-of-the-rural-fuel-rebate-scheme-call-for-information" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/proposed-extension-of-the-rural-fuel-rebate-scheme-call-for-information</a> as well as supporting records.</p><p> </p><p>Details of which individual fuel stations claiming relief under the scheme cannot be disclosed due to taxpayer confidentiality.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","2902 ; 2903","2015-06-24T16:50:18.39Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381364/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381364/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381364/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-16","Fuels: Rebates","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many fuel stations are located within the KW12 postcode area and claim relief through the fuel rebate scheme.","false","Biography information for Dr Paul Monaghan","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Dr Paul Monaghan","2677"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381365","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-22","<p>The Fair and Effective Markets Review was a joint review between the Bank of England, the Financial Conduct Authority (FCA) and HM Treasury. It was chaired by Nemat “Minouche” Shafik, Deputy Governor at the Bank of England, with Martin Wheatley (CEO of the FCA) and Charles Roxburgh (Director General Financial Services at HM Treasury) as co-chairs.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Review’s secretariat was based at the Bank of England and was drawn from all three authorities, including from HM Treasury. This has been a collaborative piece of work across the institutions and officials maintained a continuous two-way communication between the Review and HM Treasury throughout the life of the Review.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Review has concluded its findings and made recommendations to the Chancellor on 10 June. The Chancellor and the Governor of the Bank of England have welcomed the Review’s final recommendations in their Mansion House speeches. To ensure that momentum is maintained on the recommendations, the three Principals have committed to providing a full implementation update to the Chancellor and the Governor of the Bank of England, by June 2016.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2015-06-22T16:46:10.137Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381365/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381365/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381365/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-16","Fair and Effective Markets Review","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, when he last met with representatives of the (a) Financial Conduct Authority and (b) Bank of England to discuss recommendations made by the Fair and Effective Markets Review.","false","Biography information for Alison McGovern","Wirral South","Alison McGovern","2686"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381366","Cabinet Office","false","2015-06-22","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p><p> </p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson",,"2015-06-22T16:09:52.293Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381366/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381366/answer","PQ 2679 Haigh MP.pdf","PQ 2679 Haigh MP.pdf","UKSA Letter to Member - Living Wage","UKSA Letter to Member - Living Wage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381366/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-06-16","Living Wage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what estimate he has made of the number of people earning the living wage.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","2679"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381367","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-22","<p>The Government has been consistent and clear that its objective in respect of RBS ownership is to return the bank to the private sector in full.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>This policy is supported by recent advice from the Governor of the Bank of England that “it is in the public interest for the Government to begin now to return RBS to the private sector”, and that “there could be considerable net costs to taxpayers of further delaying the start of a sale”. The findings of the recently published Rothschild report into the Government’s shareholding in RBS concur with this assessment.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","2762","2015-06-22T16:47:09.307Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381367/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381367/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381367/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-16","Royal Bank of Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what representations he has received on turning the Royal Bank of Scotland into a network of stakeholder banks held in trusts for the public benefit.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","2680"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381368","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-22","<p>The information is not available.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2015-06-22T13:38:39.957Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381368/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381368/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381368/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-16","Welfare Tax Credits","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will make an estimate of the annual cost to the public purse of (a) working families tax credits and (b) child tax credits paid to those earning below the living wage.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","2681"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381370","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-22","<p>The Office for National Statistics report the total trade balance with the EU to have been -£28.5bn in 2010, -£21.7bn in 2011, -£39.5bn in 2012, -£57.3bn in 2013 and -£61.6bn in 2014.</p><p> </p><p>The trade in goods balance with the EU was -£-43.4bn in 2010, -£40.4bn in 2011, -£56.5bn in 2012, -£69.1bn in 2013 and -£78.6bn in 2014.</p><p> </p><p>The trade in services balance with the EU was £15.0bn in 2010, £18.7bn in 2011, £17.0bn in 2012, £11.8bn in 2013 and £15.4bn in 2014.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2015-06-22T16:41:56.51Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381370/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381370/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381370/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-16","UK Trade with EU","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the balance of trade between the UK and the rest of the EU was (a) overall, (b) in visible goods and (c) in invisible goods in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Michael Fabricant","Lichfield","Michael Fabricant","2808"
