"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381376","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-22","<p>The Government has an ongoing commitment to deal with abuses and ensure that these markets are fair for all who depend on them. The Chancellor has welcomed the Review’s recommendations and the Review chairs have committed to provide further detail about the implementation of these recommendations by June 2016.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Government will go through the normal processes to consider the implementation of the recommendations that fall to the UK Government.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2015-06-22T16:43:39.833Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381376/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381376/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381376/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-16","Fair and Effective Markets Review","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what responses the Government has made to the recommendations of the Fair and Effective Markets Review 2015.","false","Biography information for Alison McGovern","Wirral South","Alison McGovern","2794"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381377","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-22","<p>This government has delivered a substantial programme of reforms to the UK’s financial regulation. We have placed the Bank of England at the centre of the new architecture and established focused regulators with clear objectives.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Prudential Regulation Authority (PRA) and Financial Conduct Authority (FCA) undertake the supervision of individual firms, while the Financial Policy Committee (FPC) within the Bank of England identifies, monitors and addresses risks to the system as a whole. The FPC regularly publishes a set of indicators that it considers when formulating policy. These indicators can be found on the Bank of England’s website using the link below.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>http://www.bankofengland.co.uk/financialstability/Pages/fpc/coreindicators.aspx</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The government has recently legislated to grant the FPC new powers of direction with regard to a leverage ratio framework and the residential mortgage market. These powers will allow the FPC to take action to prevent unsustainable levels of leverage in the financial system and to address any risks to financial stability from the housing market.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2015-06-22T16:28:44.697Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381377/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381377/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381377/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-16","Financial Services","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to the Financial System Resilience Index published by the New Economics Foundation in June 2015, what plans he has to improve the resilience of the UK financial system.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","2812"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381378","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-14","<p>The Chancellor’s Spokesperson and head of the Communications team is a civil servant. The full list of Government Special Advisers will be published in due course.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2015-07-14T16:21:11.907Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381378/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381378/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381378/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-16","Treasury: Communication","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the Answers of 4 June 2015 to Questions 192 and 193, whether his Department's director of communications is a Special Adviser or a civil servant.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","2813"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381379","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-23","<p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) has a strong track record of tackling those who have evaded their responsibilities or those who have facilitated tax evasion. <br><br>In this case, HMRC and other law enforcement agencies are still in the process of re-examining data, which can now be used for criminal purposes. This follows agreement to do so from the French Authorities. The results of the re-examination will require assessment and evaluation to determine the need for any criminal or civil investigations.<br><br>HMRC is working with a range of law enforcement agencies but is unable to provide a precise timescale for completion of the task.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","2683","2015-06-23T16:19:08.817Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381379/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381379/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381379/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-16","HSBC: Tax Avoidance","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the Answer of 5 June 2015 to Question 261, when he plans next to update the House on progress with the inquiry into tax avoidance facilitated by HSBC.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","2766"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381380","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-23","<p>To provide an answer would come at a disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2015-06-23T13:10:58.49Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381380/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381380/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381380/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-16","Child Benefit: Greater Manchester","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many mothers with more than two children currently receive child benefit in (a) Denton and Reddish constituency, (b) Tameside local authority area and (c) Stockport local authority area.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","2786"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381381","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-22","<p>The Government has not undertaken an estimate of the fees payable in relation to the sale of its stake in the Royal Bank of Scotland. Further information relating to the execution of the sale will be released in due course. Details of fees paid to third parties are publicly available at www.gov.uk. All HM Treasury spending greater than £25,000 is published there too.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2015-06-22T16:40:36.44Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381381/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381381/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381381/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-16","Royal Bank of Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the fees payable to (a) law firms, (b) banks and (c) other advisers in relation to the sale of the Government's stake in the Royal Bank of Scotland.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","2682"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381382","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-23","<p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) has a strong track record of tackling those who have evaded their responsibilities or those who have facilitated tax evasion. <br><br>In this case, HMRC and other law enforcement agencies are still in the process of re-examining data, which can now be used for criminal purposes. This follows agreement to do so from the French Authorities. The results of the re-examination will require assessment and evaluation to determine the need for any criminal or civil investigations.<br><br>HMRC is working with a range of law enforcement agencies but is unable to provide a precise timescale for completion of the task.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","2766","2015-06-23T16:19:08.897Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381382/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381382/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381382/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-16","HSBC: Tax Avoidance","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the Answer of 5 June 2015 to Question 261, when he plans to make a statement to the House on progress made with the inquiry into tax avoidance.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","2683"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381383","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-23","<p>It is not possible for HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) to provide details of any contact with individuals or businesses.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-06-23T16:32:37.587Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381383/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381383/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381383/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-16","HSBC: Tax Avoidance","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the Answer of 5 June 2015 to Question 261, whether the inquiry into tax avoidance is receiving the cooperation of HSBC.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","2684"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381384","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-23","<p>The number of complaints received by HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) is published in its annual reports. The figure for the year 2014/15 will be included in their next annual report.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-06-23T16:05:22.77Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381384/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381384/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381384/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-16","Revenue and Customs: Complaints","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many complaints were made by businesses about the service provided by HM Revenue and Customs in each year since 2000.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","2713"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381385","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-22","<p>The information requested is not available.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2015-06-22T14:23:05.987Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381385/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381385/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381385/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-16","Social Security Benefits: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the number of people who will claim (a) child tax credits and (b) the child element of universal credit in (i) 2016-17, (ii) 2017-18, (iii) 2018-19 and (iv) 2019-20.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","2732"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381386","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-22","<p>The Government has been consistent and clear that its objective in respect of RBS ownership is to return the bank to the private sector in full.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>This policy is supported by recent advice from the Governor of the Bank of England that “it is in the public interest for the Government to begin now to return RBS to the private sector”, and that “there could be considerable net costs to taxpayers of further delaying the start of a sale”. The findings of the recently published Rothschild report into the Government’s shareholding in RBS concur with this assessment.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","2680","2015-06-22T16:47:09.45Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381386/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381386/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381386/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-16","Royal Bank of Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will commission a cost benefit analysis of alternatives to selling the government stake in the Royal Bank of Scotland.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","2762"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381387","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-22","<p>The Chancellor has received independent advice from the Governor of the Bank of England and from Rothschild that it is in the interests of taxpayers to begin now to sell our stake in RBS. This is the right thing to do for the economy and for British taxpayers, and to ensure the best price possible.<br><br>The Governor of the Bank of England notes that a privately owned banking sector is best able to allocate capital efficiently and competitively to grow jobs, investment and income and that there could be considerable net costs to taxpayers of further delaying the start of a sale.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2015-06-22T16:49:58.643Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381387/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381387/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381387/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-16","Royal Bank of Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the potential effect on public finances of selling the government stake in the Royal Bank of Scotland.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","2763"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381388","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-23","<p>No final decisions have yet been made as to where regional centres will be located. HM Revenue and Customs are currently considering the options and will make an announcement in due course.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","2803 ; 2804 ; 2805 ; 2806","2015-06-23T16:16:25.97Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381388/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381388/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381388/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-16","Revenue and Customs: South Yorkshire","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the Answer of 5 June 2015 to Question 196, what consideration he plans to give to the effect on the local economy of closing HM Revenue and Customs offices in South Yorkshire.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","2764"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381390","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-06-24","<p>My Department remains fully committed to the approach to creating an integrated society set out in &quot;Creating the Conditions for Integration&quot;. As detailed in the report, integration is achieved when neighbourhoods, families and individuals come together on issues that matter to them. As such, we focus on supporting shared activities to bring people together to enable strong communities where people feel they belong. We continue to support projects based on this approach, such as the community-based English language programme which enables isolated adults to learn English, and the Near Neighbours campaign, which brings together diverse faith communities to help them improve their local neighbourhoods.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2015-06-24T11:33:15.263Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381390/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381390/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381390/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-16","Community Relations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, whether the strategy set out in his Department's paper, Creating the conditions for integration, published on 21 February 2012, remains the strategy of his Department.","false","Biography information for Lyn Brown","West Ham","Lyn Brown","2696"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381391","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-06-23","<p>Statistics on adult and community learning from Skills Funding Agency grant funding in each local authority are published online in the Revenue Outturn Specific and Special Revenue Grants (RG), which are available at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/collections/local-authority-revenue-expenditure-and-financing" target="_blank">http://www.gov.uk/government/collections/local-authority-revenue-expenditure-and-financing</a></p><p> </p><p>Note that this is the level of funding from this specific grant but will not necessarily represent the full level of expenditure for adult learning within the local authority.</p><p> </p><p>Data is not currently available for 2014-15 and is not available at parliamentary constituency level.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2015-06-23T11:55:11.87Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381391/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381391/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381391/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-16","Adult Education: Greater Manchester","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how much funding has been provided for adult learning in (a) Denton and Reddish constituency, (b) Tameside local authority area and (c) Stockport local authority area in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","2784"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381392","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-06-22","<p>This information is published in the English Housing Survey 2013 to 2014: headline report. Please refer to Annex Table 1.1. in the link below:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/english-housing-survey-2013-to-2014-headline-report" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/english-housing-survey-2013-to-2014-headline-report</a></p><p> </p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2015-06-22T15:12:08.337Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381392/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381392/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381392/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-16","Owner Occupation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what proportion of households in England were owner-occupied in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Emma Reynolds","Wolverhampton North East","Emma Reynolds","2809"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381393","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-06-22","<p>The Cities and Local Government Devolution Bill is an enabling measure providing for the transfer of existing powers from one public body to another through secondary legislation. Accordingly, an impact assessment is not necessary or appropriate at this point.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2015-06-22T15:37:46.913Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381393/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381393/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381393/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-16","Cities and Local Government Devolution Bill (HL)","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what impact assessment the Government has carried out on the Cities and Local Government Devolution Bill; and if he will place a copy of that assessment in the Library.","false","Biography information for Emma Reynolds","Wolverhampton North East","Emma Reynolds","2676"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381395","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-08-05","In the light of the shocking revelations that have emerged about poor practice in recent weeks my Hon Friend the Minister for Civil Society has asked Sir Stuart Etherington, Chief Executive of the National Council of Voluntary Organisations, to chair a cross-party panel to conduct a root and branch review of the self-regulation of charitable fundraising. The panel will report back to him with their recommendations on 21 September.","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-08-05T14:04:40.007Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381395/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381395/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381395/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-06-16","Charities: Donors","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, if he will take steps to  stop charities sharing and selling information about their donors.","false","Biography information for Mr Nigel Evans","Ribble Valley","Mr Nigel Evans","2628"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381396","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-06-26","<p>No such consideration has been given as the provision of mobile coverage is a commercial decision for mobile network operators (MNOs). However the Government has taken steps to ensure that mobile coverage improves across the UK through its landmark agreement with the MNOs to guarantee voice and SMS text to at least 90% of UK landmass and the licence obligation on Telefonica to provide 4G indoor coverage to 98% of premises in the UK, both by the end of 2017.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-06-26T10:12:44.223Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381396/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381396/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381396/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-06-16","Mobile Phones: Rural Areas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what consideration the Government has given to the use of mobile repeaters to help extend mobile-coverage in rural and island areas.","false","Biography information for Mr Alistair Carmichael","Orkney and Shetland","Mr Alistair Carmichael","2795"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381397","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-06-22","<p>The Secretary of State will introduce regulations to implement the changes brought about by the recast Directive 2014/60/EU of 15 May 2014 before 18 December 2015.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-06-22T16:38:50.467Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381397/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381397/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381397/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-06-16","Cultural Heritage: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, pursuant to the contribution of 10 June 2015 from the Prime Minister, Official Report, column 1210, what steps he is taking to implement EU Directive 2014/60/EU of 15 May 2014 on the return of cultural objects unlawfully removed from the territory of a member state.","false","Biography information for Mr David Burrowes","Enfield, Southgate","Mr David Burrowes","2823"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381398","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-06-26","<p>The Minister for Culture and the Digital Economy has held two roundtables this year with a range of interested stakeholders, including consumer groups. The last one took place in March.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Government takes the issue of the nuisance telephone calls seriously and continues to work with the regulators, consumer groups and industry to co-ordinate on efforts to clamp down on such unwanted calls and protect all consumers.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-06-26T10:15:46.85Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381398/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381398/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381398/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-06-16","Direct Selling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what recent discussions he has had with consumer groups on nuisance telephone calls.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","2776"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381399","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-06-26","<p>The Government takes the issue of unsolicited telephone calls very seriously and is considering such proposals as part of its work to tackle nuisance calls, including considering options of call blocking technology.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-06-26T10:13:43.233Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381399/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381399/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381399/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-06-16","Direct Selling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, if he will bring forward proposals to require companies making unsolicited telephone calls to state their telephone numbers when they call.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","2772"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381400","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-10-01","<p>Substantial progress has been made to tackle nuisance calls. This has included ensuring improved information &amp; signposting for consumers wanting to report nuisance calls. In addition we have increase powers for the regulators. Ofcom’s monetary penalty powers increased from £50,000 to £2 million in September 2010. In July 2011, the Information Commissioner’s Office (ICO) was equipped with a new monetary penalty power of £500,000. Previously this was £5,000.</p><p> </p><p>In July 2014, Ofcom was empowered to share relevant information with the ICO that it acquired about companies breaching the regulations. And more recently, the legal threshold was lowered for the ICO on 6 April 2015, making it easier for them to take enforcement action, including issuing monetary penalties.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Government is continuing to work to ensure protection of consumers from unwanted and nuisance calls.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-10-01T15:07:53.78Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381400/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381400/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381400/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-06-16","Direct Selling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what progress he has made on preventing unwanted and nuisance telephone calls.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","2773"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381401","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-07-10","<p>Helping parents to protect their children from inappropriate and harmful content online remains a top priority, with measures implemented under the previous Government including easy to use parental control filters in the home. The Government also made a commitment in the election manifesto to require age verification for access to sites containing pornographic material. It is considering its approach to delivering this commitment, and will share its plans in due course. Ministers will engage with the UK Council for Child Internet Safety (UKCCIS) and other key stakeholders as they develop this policy.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-07-10T13:36:21.673Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381401/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381401/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381401/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-06-16","Pornography: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what steps his Department is taking to prevent young teenagers having access and becoming addicted to pornography.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","2697"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381402","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-22","<p>The UK-US defence relationship is as strong as it has ever been.</p><p>On operations, our forces have fought side by side in Iraq and Afghanistan. Today we are together combating terrorism and violent extremism in the Middle East and Africa, maintaining freedom of navigation in the Persian Gulf, providing reassurance to NATO Allies in Eastern Europe, providing training and other support for the Ukrainian Armed Forces, undertaking counter-piracy operations off the Horn of Africa, countering the narcotic trade in South America and the Caribbean, fighting Ebola in West Africa and providing nuclear deterrence for NATO.</p><p>Beyond joint operations, our collaboration spans the full spectrum of defence activity including intelligence sharing, nuclear cooperation, joint exercises and training, defence procurement, cyber, science and technology.</p><p>The US continues to value what the UK has always been able to offer: our leadership and partnership in addressing shared challenges, and a contribution to global operations that no other ally can match.</p><p>On funding, we have the largest defence budget in the EU and the second largest in NATO. We will spend 2% of our GDP on defence this year. We will invest over £160 billion over the next decade on our future force.</p><p>Our defence relationship with the US benefits from a healthy regular dialogue and strong personal relationships at the most senior levels.</p><p>Our Combined Chiefs met for the third time in recent history in the US in May to discuss our approach to shared challenges like ISIL and Russia and to ensuring that our forces are increasingly able to operate alongside each other.</p><p>When I met with the US Secretary of Defense earlier in the year he said that &quot;our military collaboration is the cornerstone of both of our nations' security&quot;. I look forward to seeing him again next week at the meeting of NATO Defence Ministers where we will continue to look for opportunities to strengthen our relationship for our mutual benefit.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2015-06-22T15:45:28.663Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381402/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381402/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381402/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-16","USA: Defence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps he is taking to strengthen the UK's relationship with the US in relation to defence operations and funding.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","2701"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381403","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-22","<p>The timing of any debate in the House on the Successor programme will be announced in due course.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-06-22T15:34:52.11Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381403/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381403/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381403/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-16","Nuclear Weapons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, in which month of 2016 his Department plans to bring before the House proposals for the Main Gate decision for the renewal of the UK's nuclear deterrent.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","2714"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381404","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-22","<p>Decisions on the cyber defence budget for 2016-17 and beyond will be reviewed as part of the forthcoming spending review.</p><p> </p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2015-06-22T15:41:34.037Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381404/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381404/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381404/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-16","Electronic Warfare: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what his Department's cyber defence budget will be in each year from 2016-17 to 2019-20.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","2715"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381405","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-22","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 2 June 2015 to Question 428 to the hon. Member for St. Helens North (Mr McGinn).</p><p>http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2015-05-28/428/</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-06-22T15:40:40.413Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381405/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381405/answer","Hansard Extract HOC 428.doc","Hansard Extract HOC 428.doc","Armed Forces Covenant","Armed Forces Covenant","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381405/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-16","Armed Forces Covenant","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the regional distribution of money raised by fines issued for Libor manipulation has been in each year since its introduction.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","2716"
