"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381411","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-22","<p>The Royal Navy currently has no dedicated harbour training ships; all ships conduct training as part of their generation and operation.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-06-22T15:48:29.71Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381411/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381411/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381411/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-16","Type 23 Frigates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many Type 23 frigates are harbour training ships; and what the name is of each such ship.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","2642"
